[Nouns] lenity, lenience, leniency; moderation [more]; tolerance, toleration; mildness, gentleness; favor, indulgence, indulgency; clemency, mercy, forbearance, quarter; compassion [more].
[Verbs] be lenient; tolerate, bear with; parcere subjectis, give quarter.
indulge, allow one to have his own way, spoil.
[Adjectives] lenient; mild, mild as milk; gentle, soft; tolerant, indulgent, easy-going; clement (compassionate) [more]; forbearing; long-suffering.
